Trudeau and his Liberal minority government have been shocked by and unprepared for the scope and sustained nature of the ongoing, nationwide solidarity actions and blockades in support of the hereditary chiefs of the Wet’suwet’en (for more on Wet’suwet’en resistance).
The backlash was provoked by the Royal Canadian Mounted Police’s invasion of Wet’suwet’en territory on February 7, and the arrest of 24 land defenders.
TC Energy has rejected a proposed route that would take the pipeline around Wet’suwet’en territory.
But a new difficulty for Trudeau is the level of potential opposition to this project within his own party.
Trudeau and big business will try to pit workers against one another and against the land defenders.